# No Breaking Changes to Database or API

## Hard Rules

**Database**
- NEVER add, remove, or rename columns in existing tables
- NEVER change column types or constraints in existing tables
- NEVER drop or rename existing tables
- If new data storage is needed, add new tables only

**Existing API Endpoints**
- NEVER remove or rename existing endpoints
- NEVER change the meaning or type of existing request/response fields
- NEVER make previously optional parameters required
- NEVER change existing authentication/authorization requirements on existing endpoints

## Allowed (Additive Only)

- Add NEW endpoints
- Add NEW optional query parameters with sensible defaults so old callers are unaffected
- Add NEW fields to existing JSON responses (clients ignore unknown fields)
- Add NEW tables to the database
- Add NEW config/option keys

## Why

Other projects depend on this project's API. Any breaking change will silently break those integrations.

## Examples

```go
// ✅ OK — new optional param with default, old callers unaffected
days := 30
if daysStr := c.Query("days"); daysStr != "" { ... }

// ❌ BAD — renaming existing field breaks clients
// "token_count" → "total_tokens"

// ✅ OK — add new field alongside existing ones
gin.H{"existing_field": x, "new_field": y}

// ❌ BAD — ALTER TABLE existing column
// ALTER TABLE logs MODIFY COLUMN model_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
```
